<section xml:id="section-runestone">
  <title>Runestone Academy</title>
  <p>
    Our book and online homework is hosted at a site called Runestone Academy. You will need an
    account with Runestone Academy. Visit
    <url href="https://runestone.academy/" visual="runestone.academy">Runestone Academy</url> and
    click to Log In/Sign Up. The username you create may not contain a dot like your PCC username
    might have. When you sign up, the <q>Course Name</q> you need to use is
    <c>portlandcommunitycollege_orcca_fall23</c>.
  </p>
  <paragraphs>
    <title>Textbook</title>
    <p>
      The textbook is usually where you land when you are logged in to Runestone Academy. Our class
      covers chapters 1<ndash/>4. There are embedded <q>Checkpoint</q> exercises in each section,
      and completing these is part of your homework assignments.
    </p>
  </paragraphs>
  <paragraphs>
    <title>Assignments</title>
    <p>
      Your assignments for each section include the <q>Checkpoint</q> exercises,
      <q>Reading Questions</q>, and <em>some</em> of the regular exercises at the end of each
      section. To get to an assignment, use the little person icon at the top of a page to visit
      <q>Assignments</q>. Here you will see all three types of exercise grouped together.
    </p>
    <p>
      Assignments are due the Sunday night after we cover a section in class. See
      <xref ref="section-calendar"/> for the schedule. You typically get an additional two weeks
      beyond the due date to complete these assignments, however you should not rely on that. The
      official due dates keep you from falling so far behind that you fail the course.
    </p>
  </paragraphs>
